Vice President Biden released a statement on the 10th anniversary of the International Day for the Elimination of Violence Against Women. He emphasized that violence against women is a global problem that can be prevented. He mentioned examples such as gang rape in times of war, domestic violence, and human trafficking. Biden highlighted that this violence hinders women's and girls' potential, causes immense suffering, and has significant social and economic costs. He called on all Americans to join the international community in advocating for an end to these abuses.